<bioghist encodinganalog="545">
<p>The Freemason Golden Rule Lodge No. 159 was formed in Ann Arbor, Michigan in 1865. In 1927, the lodge had 1036 members. From this high mark, membership would decline to 516 in 1979. In the 1990s, among the charitable organizations supported by the Lodge was the Juvenile Diabetes Foundation. The Lodge also provided scholarships for area high school students.</p>
</bioghist>



<scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
<p>The records of the Golden Rule Lodge No. 159, Ann Arbor, Michigan include minutes of the special and regular meetings of the lodge, membership materials, by-laws, and some financial records. Included is a volume of memorial programs for past state grand masters.</p>
</scopecontent>

